      • BGTDatabase

        public BGTDatabase​(DatabaseOptions dbOptions)
            throws ClassNotFoundException
        Create a BGTDatabase that will load the driver and create a database connection.
        Parameters:
        dbOptions - Database connection options.
        Throws:
        ClassNotFoundException - If the JDBC driver could not be loaded.

      • BGTDatabase

        public BGTDatabase​(DatabaseOptions dbOptions,
                   Connection connection)
            throws SQLException
        Create a BGTDatabase with a supplied Connection without loading the driver and making connections here. The connection string in DatabaseOptions is not used, it is retrieved from the supplied Connection to determine the dialect.
        Parameters:
        dbOptions - Database options - not used for making connections
        connection - Connection to use, must not be closed. Connection will be closed by CLI classes after processing, override the close() method to avoid that.
        Throws:
        SQLException
